        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Since we need to fit the emission feature to obtain the fine doppler shift velocity, line structure should be resolved well.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We have already performed a preliminary analysis using ALMA archive which has 0.5" angular resolution. In turn, Neptune has only 2.2" angular diamiter. We have detected the spatial feature which has smaller spatial scale than the synthesized beam. Therefore, to confirm such the sparial feature of HCN distribution and wind, well-resolved observation, which can resolve alredy-found spatial feature clearly is needed. 0.1" resolution was determined to resolve the newly-found feature.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Since our target line HCN has only 5 km/s HWHM, bandwidth needed here is determined by the frequency resolution. From our preliminary analysis of ALMA archive data, 0.5 MHz frequency resolution is enough to achive 100 m/s velocity error for 500 m/s wind. 
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
